main event: A military observer spotted circular and flat discs moving in the sky at Eglin AFB, Florida, on March 23, 1967.
interesting points: The objects appeared circular and flat, white in distance and silver when close,Observations described formations resembling a flight of birds, with hundreds of individual particles involved,The observer first spotted the formations through his car windshield at approximately 45 degrees elevation,The sightings were made during clear and sunny weather conditions,The preliminary analysis suggested that the sighting could be explained by the reflection of chaff from a USN aircraft.
witness description: Military observer George W. Kaelin, A1C, working in flight management at Eglin AFB.
